  "prompt": "Which is a good refrence book for Servlets and JSP?",
  "response": "A highly recommended reference book for Servlets and JSP is \"Head First Servlets and JSP\" by Bryan Basham, Kathy Sierra, and Bert Bates. This book is known for its engaging style and comprehensive coverage, making complex concepts more understandable with its visually rich format and hands-on examples.\n\nAdditionally, \"Core Servlets and JavaServer Pages\" by Marty Hall and Larry Brown is another excellent resource. It provides detailed explanations and practical examples, making it suitable for both beginners and experienced developers.\n\nBoth books cover the fundamentals and advanced topics, ensuring a strong understanding of Servlets and JSP.",
